## Common Patterns
- **Repository Pattern**: Abstract data access with interfaces
- **Use Case Pattern**: Encapsulate business operations
- **Dependency Injection**: Inject dependencies through constructors
- **Error Boundaries**: React error handling for UI
- **Form Management**: React Hook Form for form handling

## File Naming
- **Components**: PascalCase.tsx (e.g., CustomerCard.tsx)
- **Hooks**: useCamelCase.ts (e.g., useCustomer.ts)
- **Utilities**: camelCase.ts (e.g., apiClient.ts)
- **Types**: PascalCase.ts (e.g., Customer.ts)
- **Interfaces**: IPascalCase.ts (e.g., ICustomerRepository.ts)

## Environment Variables
- **Backend**: PORT, MONGODB_URI, JWT_SECRET, NODE_ENV
- **Frontend**: VITE_API_URL, VITE_APP_NAME
- **Never commit**: .env files, secrets, API keys

## Git Workflow
- **Branches**: feature/, bugfix/, hotfix/, release/
- **Commits**: Conventional commits (feat:, fix:, docs:, etc.)
- **Review**: All code must be reviewed before merge
- **CI/CD**: Automated testing and deployment

## Performance
- **Backend**: Database indexing, connection pooling, caching
- **Frontend**: Lazy loading, React.memo, bundle optimization
- **Database**: Proper queries, pagination, aggregation

## Security
- **Authentication**: JWT tokens with expiration
- **Authorization**: Role-based access control
- **Validation**: Input sanitization and validation
- **Secrets**: Environment variables, no hardcoded secrets

## Testing
- **Unit Tests**: Business logic and utilities
- **Integration Tests**: API endpoints and database
